message: The 'filter' tool is your best friend for initial 'gas' and 'liquid' ingredients; it reliably turns them into 30-value items. However, applying the 'filter' to 'solid' ingredients or using the 'vial' tool almost always leads to negative values and 'botched' features. Avoid combining many items, and especially avoid combining solids with anything, as it tends to create highly negative value items. Once you have a 30-value item, you're usually safe to submit if further actions are too risky.
